e-rates in both the SDR and HDR domains, which results in easy and efficient workflows — for example, no requirement to decode to a raw pixel format.","type":"text"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-304-Explore-video-experiences-for-visionOS":{"title":"Explore video experiences for visionOS","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-304-Explore-video-experiences-for-visionOS","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-304-explore-video-experiences-for-visionos","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about the different ways you can create and present immersive video experiences within your app. We’ll explore the diverse media types available in visionOS 26, including profiles for 180°, 360°, and wide FOV video; options for creating and playing Apple Immersive Video; and expanded capabilities for 2D, 3D, and spatial video. Discover which profiles are best for your app and its content."}],"kind":"article"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","title":"WWDC25","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","type":"card"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"AlarmKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"PermissionKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and more.","type":"text"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/avfoundation/converting-projected-video-to-apple-projected-media-profile":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"this sample application"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/avfoundation\/converting-projected-video-to-apple-